-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-29/ghana-s-gridco-to-raise-230-million-from-banks-graphic-says.html
Ghana Grid Co. , a state-owned power
transmission company, will raise $230 million from local and
international banks this year to invest in infrastructure,
Graphic reported.  The company, also known as Gridco, will receive 80 million
euros ($115.1 million) from French companies Coface and Societe
Generale SA, $70 million from Export-Import Bank of  Korea , $25
million from Standard Chartered Bank Plc and $13 million from
Cal Bank Ltd. of  Ghana , the Accra-based newspaper said, citing
Charles Darku, chief executive officer of the company.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 